Nate noted at the end that the foam on top of the water looked metallic. I have a hypothesis about that. One of the biggest ingredients in matches is an oxide of manganese, a silvery-gray metal. This oxide releases, of course, oxygen when it is heated to a very high temperature, providing one of the ingredients in the fire triangle. What remains is usually metallic manganese with most of the oxygen stripped away.
